data.description: This stunning home checks all of the boxes and is a must see. It is located in a quiet cul-de-sac on one of the nicest streets in all of Brunswick Plantation. From your back porch and many windows in the house, you will enjoy panoramic golf course views as well as amazing sunsets over the pond. This floorplan is very functional and offers 4 bedrooms on 1 level! The ceilings in the living room are vaulted and there are built in bookshelves and cabinets on either side of the fireplace. The kitchen is adjacent to the living room and features ample cabinet space with a really nice backsplash and of course granite counter tops and stainless-steel appliances. This home is great for entertaining as you have space for a breakfast table and barstool seating at the kitchen island. For the more formal settings, there is a large dining room off of the kitchen. The oversized primary bedroom easily accommodates a king size bed and is highlighted by a large walk-in closet. The ensuite bath has a jetted tub and shower as well as two vanities with make up vanity in between. On the opposite side of the house, you will find the three guest bedrooms and the guest bath. Each of these guest rooms are a good size and for those who want a home office, one of the bedrooms is perfect for that! There is also a half bath for guests to use, located next to the laundry room. Perhaps the best room in the house is the bright sunroom located in the back of the house, complete with a wet bar! You will find yourself enjoying this room year-round as you take in the views. For storage you have a two-car garage and a walk-up attic. The attic was built in a way that you could finish it and turn it into a bonus room with bath. Plumbing rough ins are there as well as electric. There is a lot of detail in this house that you have to see to appreciate. It is great condition and ready for the next owner to begin enjoying. Residents enjoy 27 holes of golf, indoor & outdoor pools, a fitness center and more!
